adds data reference only if it not already present. This method takes a hit primarily because it searches for the occurence of a similar data reference before adding it. It is faster to create a group with an array of references.

filterBy

filter on the pathname using regular expression. The current group is left to contain only those expressions that have the regular expression in them.

filterBy

public void filterBy(Predicate<DataReference> predicate,
                     boolean selecting)
filters on this group using filter. This causes the reference list held by this group to be modified. This change is physically reflected by appending the filter expression string to the name of this group.
